  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis accumulation model employs the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law correlation, which is theoretically valid under the assumption that erythrocyte damage accumulates linearly and independently across Lagrangian fluid pathlines — i.e., the damage contributions from successive sub-exposures are additive and path-independent. This linearity-of-damage-accumulation assumption is a well-known theoretical precondition for the Lagrangian strain-history integration method used here.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "conformsToProfileDetail": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileComplete",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
