      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-01-benchmark-nominal",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Benchmark hemolysis validation at nominal operating point",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA in-vitro measurements for the generic centrifugal pump at the nominal design point (5 L/min, 2400 RPM). Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law with Lagrangian pathline integration yields NIH = 0.0031 g/100 L versus experimental 0.0034 g/100 L; relative error 9%. Validation performed at a single steady operating condition where shear stress history along pathlines is relatively uniform, a regime in which the linear damage-accumulation assumption is not challenged by recirculating or highly unsteady flow structures.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Relative error in NIH = 9% at nominal point",
      "validationStatus": "passed"
    },
    {
