      "rationale": "NIH is the primary computational output; RH is derived by normalizing against predicate device NIH. Both quantities directly support the RH < 1 regulatory acceptance criterion. The power-law exponent and coefficient in the Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation are assumed constant across the COU operating range, consistent with the linear accumulation precondition but not independently verified for off-nominal conditions."
    },
