      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis sub-model selection must be justified by literature precedent for blood pump CFD at the Reynolds numbers of the COU.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on established literature precedent for centrifugal blood pump CFD (Re ~ 10^4). Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation selected as the standard regulatory benchmark model. The correlation is theoretically applicable when erythrocyte damage accumulates linearly and independently along Lagrangian pathlines — a precondition that holds in steady, attached-flow regimes. The COU includes operating points at reduced flow (2 L/min, 3500 RPM) where separated flow and recirculation are anticipated; applicability of the linear accumulation assumption in this sub-regime is noted in the literature as an open question but is not evaluated here."
    },
